gurmukhi: ਸੀਚ ਬਾਰ ਪੁਨ ਤਾਹਿ ਜਗਾਯੋ || ਜਗੇ ਮੂਰਛਨਾ ਪੁਨ ਜੀਯ ਅਾਯੋ ||
transliteration: Seech Baar Poun Taah(i) Jagadyo|| Jage Moondchhanaa Poun Jeeya Aayo||
translation: Narsingh sprinkled ambrosia and woke him up from the unconscious state and he become alert after coming out of the state of unconsciousness.

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁਰੋ ਭਿਰੇ ਸੂਰ ਦੋੲੀ ਕ੍ਰੁੱਧਾ || ਮੰਡਯੋ ਬਹੁਰ ਅਾਪ ਮਹਿ ਜੁੱਧਾ ||੩੭||
transliteration: Bahuro Bhire Soor Doikruddhaa|| Mandyo Bahur Aap Maih Juddhaa||37||
translation: Both the heroes began to fight again furiously and a dreadful war began again.37.

gurmukhi: ਹਲਾ ਚਾਲ ਕੈ ਕੈ ਪੁਨਰ ਬੀਰ ਢੂਕੇ || ਮਚਯੋ ਜੁੱਧ ਜਯੋ ਕਰਨ ਸੰਗੰ ਘੜੂਕੇ ||
transliteration: Halaa Dhaal Kai Kai Pounar Beer Dhooke|| Machyo Juddh Jyo Karan Sanadg Ghadooke||
translation: After challenging each other, both the heroes began to fight again, and a dreadful war ensued between them for gaining victory over the other.

gurmukhi: ਨਖੰ ਪਾਤ ਦੋੳੂ ਕਰੇ ਦੈਤ ਘਾਤੰ || ਮਨੋ ਗੱਜ ਜੁੱਟੇ ਬਨੰ ਮਸਤ ਮਾਤੰ ||੩੮||
transliteration: Nakhannddpaat Dooo Dare Dait Ghaatan|| Mano Gadj Joutte Banan Mast Maatan||38||
translation: Both of them were giving destructive blows to one another with their nails and appeared like two intoxicated elephants fighting each other in the forest.38.

gurmukhi: ਪੁਨਰ ਨਾਰ ਸਿੰਘੰ ਧਰਾ ਤਾਹਿ ਮਾਰਯੋ || ਪਰਾਨੋ ਪਲਾਸੀ ਮਨੋ ਬਾੲਿ ਡਾਰਯੋ ||
transliteration: Pounar Naar Singhan Dharaa Taab(i) Mdaryo|| Puraano Palaasimano Bade Ddaryo||
translation: Narsingh again threw Hiranayakashipu on the earth just as the old Palas tree (Butea frondosa) falls down on the earth with a gust of wind.

gurmukhi: ਹਨਯੋ ਦੇਖ ਦੁਸਟੰ ਭੲੀ ਪੁਹਪ ਬਰਖੰ || ਕੀੲੇ ਦੇਵਤਯੋ ਅਾਨਕੈ ਜੀਤ ਕਰਖੰ ||੩੯||
transliteration: Hanyo Dekh Doustan Bhaipuhap Barakhannd|| Keee Devtyo Aankai Jeet Karakhannd||39||
translation: Seeing that tyrants hath died, sang many types of songs of victory.39.

gurmukhi: ਕੀਨੌ ਨ੍ਰਸਿੰਘ ਦੁਸਟੰ ਸੰਘਾਰ || ਧਰਯੋ ਸੁ ਬਿਸਨ ਸਪਤਮ ਵਤਾਰ ||
transliteration: Keenau Nrasingh Doustan Sanhaar|| Ddaryo Su Bisan Satam Vataar||
translation: Narsingh destroyed the tyrant and in this way Vishnu manifested his seventh incarnation.

gurmukhi: ਲਿੱਨੋ ਸੁ ਭਗਤ ਅਪਨੋ ਛਿਨਾੲਿ || ਸਭ ਸਿਸਟ ਧਰਮ ਕਰਮਨ ਚਲਾੲਿ ||੪੦||
transliteration: Linno Su Bhagad Apno Chhinaae|| Sabh Sist Dharam Karman Chadhaae||40||
translation: He protected his devotee and spread righteousness on the earth.40.

gurmukhi: ਪ੍ਹਲਾਦ ਕਰਯੋ ਨ੍ਰਿਪ ਛੱਤ੍ਰ ਫੇਰ || ਦੀਨੋ ਸੰਘਾਰ ਸਭ ੲਿਮ ਅੰਧੇਰ ||
transliteration: Prahlaad Daryo Nrip Chhattra Phr|| Deeno Sanhaar Sabh Im Andher||
translation: The canopy was swung over the head of Prahlad and he was made a king, and in this way, the demons, who were darkness-incarnate, were destroyed.
